Daily menu of an obese child: no breakfast and dinner with sausages
More than one third of children aged 9 to 13 are overweight, with overweight affecting 9% of the school population and obesity affecting 5%.
Obese children are mostly from families with unhealthy lifestyles, according to current research.
The importance of the environment in which one grows up for the healthy development of the person is again demonstrated, as well as the models that serve as a reference.
At the table, obese children eat, for example, at least twice as often as children from normal-weight families.
For dinner, more than 19 percent of the obese had eaten fries the day before the test, which is linked to the "Obesity Is Not a Chance" prevention program.
In families of overweight children there is no habit of practicing sports, which is applicable to most of the current families, where only 15% of children answered that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was carried out at the end of the last school year and involved almost 900 children from all over the Czech Republic.
It was the second edition of the "Obesity is not a coincidence" program, which is supported by the General Health Insurance Company and the Unilever company.
So far, more than 12,000 children from the 4th to the 8th grade have participated in the project.
Proper diet and sufficient exercise in the family are determining factors, which cause a marked decrease in the number of overweight and even obese children.
"Only half of the children surveyed said they had five meals a day according to the regimen: breakfast, lunch, dinner, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet", says one of the survey results.
No breakfast but with stew for dinner
Specialists warn that in healthy development, details are important, such as having a fixed time for breakfast in the family.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of schoolchildren's families eat breakfast at the same time.
In most families, everyone eats breakfast alone.
But the worst part was finding out that 10% of the households don't eat breakfast at all.
Breakfast, however, is the basis of a proper daily diet.
The study shows that the families of obese children consume the unhealthy French fries much more often.
Almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sugary soft drinks daily (70%).
Overall, more than 40% of the children surveyed do sports, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15%.
Make your own diet
The next phase of the study allowed the selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"Food preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15 are, from the point of view of healthy eating, far from ideal".
Among his favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"The popularity of soft drinks is particularly alarming", warns the study's final report.
The main meal is palm paste, closely followed by bird meat.
Practically, children always reject legumes and the taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Changing to Healthy Habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they are given the right information.
"In the control group of study participants who completed the questionnaire after the end of the prevention programme 'Obesity is not a coincidence', there was in many cases a significant shift in favour of the principles of healthy eating", the study results state.
For example, the issue of soft drinks is noteworthy, as many children would prefer plain water.
Children would also more often choose poultry and fish for their main meal and restrict their consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
The stylist must also be a good psychologist, say the professionals
In the introductory article, How Stylists Learn, I already complained a bit that the initial lessons were already quite loaded.
I had no idea how that was gonna go.
Lectures by three professionals in the business, how to dress problem characters and, in addition, a seminar on how it works in the entertainment world.
And it will get worse.
The closer the final exams are, the more information and practical assignments await us.
And although the course is held every Saturday and Sunday, there's no room for a pin anymore.
We've been studying with the head teacher, Alena, (there are no men in the course) on how to dress the woman who doesn't have perfect symmetry.
And so is the vast majority.
Some are short-necked, some have a stylized figure without the proper curves, and some are overweight.
The stylist must be able to smooth out broad shoulders, lengthen a neck, or recreate the necessary curves
We've been given some tricks on how to make the body of a Jennifer Lopez type of woman stand out, with huge breasts and hips but a tight waist, and at the same time not dress her in too much of a provocative way.
If, for example, the difference between your waist and your hips is so great that your skirt or pants don't fit, it's worth having at least one extra piece of fabric tailored to your size.
They'll certainly not regret it, because clothes that fit perfectly are priceless.
A custom skirt will feel much better than one that keeps moving, standing up, dancing on the waist, etc.
The stylized body may be allowed to wear folded, ornamented, embroidered or draped clothing.
There are certainly many different kinds of information and bodies, so I'm glad I have all week to put all this information in order in my head.
And even so, I'm afraid with the assignment, I've already got more than enough.
Each participant in the course has been assigned two celebrities, who will have to design two costumes: one for the day and one for the night.
The current look, the fashion style that suits the person in question, must be taken into account.
I got to dress Miranda Kerr, you might know her from the Victoria's Secret campaign.
I'm a screamer, for me, much better than, say, Britney Spears or Christina Aguilera, who has recently gained about a hundred kilos (please note the exaggeration), or the very young Selena Gomez.
We have to cut out dresses from magazines or search the Internet and print them, and then we have to draw them out graphically.
The moodboard, which is what the whole result is called, also expresses our personal style and our relationship with graphic design.
It's also important to think about the graphic part of stylism.
The stylist, therefore, not only dresses physically, but also deals, for example, with the product pages in magazines (of specific topics, such as trends, bags, coats, etc.).
All this was discussed by stylist and designer Mario Kameník.
But this is all for Sunday.
The stylist has to have a global vision.
The three expert guests brought the Saturday lecture to life with information on all kinds of bodies.
The stylist Honza Pokorný, the fashion designer Jakub Polanka and the fashion photographer Ben Renč.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion and the stylist should know how to take advantage of this.
And a good stylist knows how to work with the same garment in different ways.
Variability is, in this case, fundamental.
Thus, the trench coat can be dressed classically with jeans and a T-shirt, but it also serves to dress the naked body with heels and photograph it as if it were actually a dress.
Or you can just roll it up and raise your neck to get a totally different image.
"Play with it", he insisted.
The advice I value most is this: "To get started, you need to know all the rules first".
"Then you can break them", said Jakub.
I finally understand why we memorize all these formulas, what is combined with what, why, if it turns out later in fashion magazines we find different results.
Not to mention the fashion shows.
Thanks to photographer Ben, I know a stylist has to have more types of clothes in stock than he's meant to photograph.
So, for a fashion story to have ten pages (hence, ten outfits), you have to have at least fifteen ready-to-wear outfits.
And also that the photos the clothes work in combination with other garments, all of them different from the ones that are worn in reality.
All of this must be taken into account when designing the outfit.
Honza Pokorný assured us that image and style alone, in many cases, represent half of the success.
Just look at Madonna, who is not exactly a great singer, but the image and the marketing have made her a world star.
In the Czech Republic, there is no clear trend towards using stylists' services at the moment.
Even famous characters also find it useless (my skills are enough, my physical appearance is not so important).
And when someone asks for our services, we must bear in mind that it is very likely that they will indicate a size very different from their actual (smaller) size.
Then you just Google it and find out if the heart magazines have already written about the topic, if a certain celebrity has gained weight, etc.
On Sunday, Honza and Mario insisted that stylists should not just focus on fashion, but also understand the concept of outfit.
During your work, you must above all communicate with the people you are wearing, so it is essential to be a good psychologist.
He values people, he doesn't look down on them, he defends their opinions.
"When a director hires you to sort out her wardrobe and fill it with beautiful clothes, you can't just take it all and throw it away and say, 'Oh, what a horror.'"
"Find at least a couple of things that you can think about and recommend for someone to wear", Mario says.
He also showed us that everything must fit in the so-called "placovka", that is, the work bag.
This one is fixed around the waist and you have all the necessary tools there.
There are also nylon threads (which serve the stylist during the photo session of products such as bags or hats), special clothing grippers for the front, if this was larger (pins and other types of grip are not allowed, as they could damage the fabric), or a sewing set.
To avoid being passive listeners and to put something into practice, we have learned to put on the soles of our shoes.
Even during studio photo shoots, on a flat surface, the sole could be damaged and much more so the exterior.
And all we did was coat and coat.
We couldn't touch the shoes with the scissors so we wouldn't damage them by accident.
So you had to be very clever.
Mario has given me a joy by praising my work without reservation.
I'm not really good at those things.
This is just a small part of all that we have heard during the whole weekend, in the second part of the course.
I've come to realize that pursuing styling professionally is not a rosy path, but I don't care what people say.
In Need for Speed: The Run, he competes across America.
Summary
A seemingly carefree trip is complicated by a series of carelessness unsuited to a routine morning shift.
The Commission has already made a number of proposals to the Council, and I am sure that the Council will be able to accept them.
The new installment, to which The Run is added, aroused great expectations even before its premiere.
It promised to give a new air to the old racing saga Need for Speed and, as a result of what was shown, it appears as a game that should not end up being again a genre of action without more.
We were also curious to see what the inserted scenes would look like, where the main character gets out of the car and walks on his own feet.
As is often the case with NFS series, the results do not vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be considered acceptable, but in the total count points are lost due to absurd errors, which have already been appearing in the series for years.
In reality, we cannot call them errors, but rather the incomprehensible reluctance of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to participate in an illegal race across America.
You're driving on the West Coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to get to New York first.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
Thus, you do not even remotely get the feeling that the game is always offering the same thing.
Some of the environments are even pleasing to the eye, although the technical level of the graphic is equivalent to that of previous installments of the series.
So it's not out of this world.
But a walk in the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-capped mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
Furthermore, careers are sometimes diversified by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you encounter a sandstorm that reduces visibility.
But in the mountains, you have to be careful not to be buried by an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There's only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to overtake a required number of rivals (the norm in a classic race), then you try to gain time (classic timed duel) and then a duel against a single opponent awaits you.
In the midst of all this, the police sometimes appear, which only makes things more difficult.
The new thing is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape from someone and you have to help him, always pressing the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than might be expected (there are actually only three).
But the end result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving pattern follows the trail of the previous episodes.
That means that today it is no longer a big deal, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you're looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a race designed with a lot of action is well suited to this style of driving, although we may find something better among the competing games.
So far, all is well.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, the same is no longer true with collisions.
Games of this kind cannot be expected to recreate complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before a hit against any object, you can not predict how your car will react, so not everything is in order.
Typically, when you're overtaking a tight overtaking or driving in normal traffic, there are only slight bumps, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up doing uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or even completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no major problems arise, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The resets are programmed in such a way that when you have an accident or go off the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, in each race there are only five resets available.
If you consume all of them, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it's just a little help in case something goes wrong, but it's not very reliable.
Sometimes it doesn't even help to reset, it just helps to learn the given stage by heart.
A big disadvantage of the game is that the same events repeat themselves in different places.
Some curves, for example, have to be entered in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find yourself in a place where "civilian" vehicles are always in the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or arrive five minutes earlier or later.
This is especially irritating in situations where you see two cars coming into the intersection in opposite directions, your opponent is easily ahead, but when you get there, you must turn or brake.
It doesn't matter when you arrive, because it's programmed so that the "surprise" will always happen right under your nose.
The adversaries have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will come to places where, regardless of the moment, the same opponent will always overtake you in the same place.
And this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must get there before you, no matter the cost.
When it's in front of you, it makes it difficult to see the cars coming in front of you, so at first you can make a mess of the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that you are likely to be disappointed right away.
And it's a shame, because even though the travel model is simple, the game is fun and action packed, so it's often not possible to follow in detail what's happening or where.
And it really doesn't matter, whether the credit goes to the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or the qualifying in the race to keep boredom out, or whatever.
An unusual idea is to change cars during races.
You have to be careful at the gas pumps on the side of the road, because that's where you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will be satisfied with what you have.
Cars fall into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for urban areas, American muscle cars for straight highways and exotic super sports cars for technical driving, for example, on curvy mountain roads.
In addition to the main narrative thread, there is also a parallel thread of challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know from the stories.
Here you'll get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which is good for both challenges and stories.
At the top level, the driver is presented with several options, starting with the car and ending with the background for the profile.
At the same time, an Autolog online feature is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and makes other community features available.
One of the hardest elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
You drive to the subway tunnel (pass), where you run around the tracks in the dark (pass).
The speedometer puts you between 90 and 120 miles per hour, and then suddenly the subway car arrives behind you and just takes you away.
In the newsroom we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game no one thought even a little or whether the authors really take us for a bunch of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the overall visual effects result in most cases pleasant, sometimes even superb.
It is a pity that in the most tense moments the quality of the image is reduced, and sometimes seriously.
This is particularly true of accidents involving many participants, when the continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
To please the majority of the youth group, the soundtrack falls into the "every man for his father and mother" category, but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game for its music alone.
The final feel of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely stupid mistakes, we would have trouble claiming that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not over.
The fun is assured, but prepare for mistakes to hit you in the eye with the force of airport searchlights.
The choirs of the Carolina University will participate in the concert "Students of Velvet".
The joint celebration of International Students' Day and the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festa Academica festival.
Twenty high school and college choirs will perform.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17th.
"Carolina University has a high turnout at the festival".
The current choirs include the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, and the festival committee includes the rector Václav Hampl", said the head of the organization, Jakub Čaloun.
The highlight of the festival is the free entry for all the public to the concert of the high school choirs, which will be held on March 17 at 14 hours in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program features the participation of Czech jazz musician Karel Růžička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening, the concert "Students of Velvet" will be held in the Municipal House in Vynohrady, with the participation of university choirs, including the choir of the University of Carolina.
The purpose of the Festa Academica is not only to celebrate the International Students' Day and the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present the choir music to the public at the highest level and to encourage collaborative creation among young people.
The main organiser is the Czech Choral Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler Secondary School.
All events were supported by the Mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the Rector of the Carolina University, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the celebratory concerts, a whole series of musical events, improvised performances by students and morning concerts.
Further information can be found on the festival website www.festaacademica.cz
