Women's worst vices: Do they apply to you too?
If you ask men to be able to name some typical vices of women, in general each of them will name them without thinking.
Dear women, do you recognize them in the following lines, where certain female vices are mentioned that manage to boil the blood of men?
Going shopping
You blame your orange half for being a shopping addict?
Does he have to buy at least one trapito a week?
Do you like to shop at the auction often?
Then in your case you can say that shopping has become a vice.
Some women realize that they should temper their passion for shopping, at least a little.
But what woman could resist the temptation to just wander through clothing stores, pick out clothes that fit well, and then try them all on in the fitting room (ideally in all different colors)?
While shopping is a pastime for most women, it can become practically hell for men.
Just remember how many times you've told your partner to wait for you outside the door.
The Constant Discontent
"Am I not too fat?"
"I need to lose at least ten pounds - should I start exercising?"
"Do you really like me?"
Do these phrases ring a bell?
That you do?
So you're one of those women who's obsessed with her looks.
Not that you should neglect your body, but many men are allergic to hearing their mate complain about her physical appearance all the time.
The stronger sex also agrees that the more the frequency of complaints increases, the more annoying women become.
Order and Cleanliness First
It's like an infinite loop.
Clean the windows, vacuum, scrub the floor, dust off, scrub the tub and all that at least twice a week.
Do you blame your spouse for treading on a clean floor with a dirty foot, your children for dirtying a freshly cleaned sink, and a shelf with glass doors that you have worked so hard to clean?
