Making unpleasant comments
"Used underpants are left with dirty clothes".
"You want to wear those used socks tomorrow, too?"
"Wet cloth is not left on the floor!"
If you do that to your partner more than once a day, you'll get him out of his head.
You don't mean anything bad, you just want to get everything in order.
Perhaps if men knew this, women, for their part, would not make so many comments.
Slander and gossip
Some women are also good at slander, gossip, but also offending and conspiring against someone.
Women focus on relationships, so they like to talk together about things like who, where, with whom, how and why.
Maybe each of us occasionally misses a little harmless gossip.
With the hand on the heart, this is typical of almost all women.
On the other hand, there are gossipy women who are not in control, who love to gossip and do it often, they despise everyone and are dangerous to those around them, especially in a female work team.
