"I've already spoken to some people I might consider".
"It was crazy to me to hear some say that they don't even want to identify with Czech football at the moment".
"I'd like to change that view", he adds.
What is supposedly most bothering Paclík at the moment is Pelta's relationship with the President of the Pilsen Regional Football Association Roman Berbr, a man with a controversial past, known outside the world as a powerful lobbyist with the ability to influence the voting of delegates in the general assembly.
