This was the work of the caretaker who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A lofoscopist from Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is key.
On November 4, a lofoscopist from the CTI in Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the identity of the top FARC chief: "Alfonso Cano", through the comparison of his fingerprints.
Of the seven lofoscopists who work in the CTI section, that week Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the area of judicial investigation for 21 years, was on duty.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in Chocó municipalities, where many times he had to intern for more than five days in the jungle to reach the site where the corpses were to be identified.
In 2000 he moved to the capital of the Valley and, after doing the corresponding courses, he specialized in lofoscopy, which is the study of the friction skin, that is, the palms of the hands and the feet.
The week of the operation against Alfonso Cano, Eliazar was warned to wear minimal clothing for three days.
Something big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for Cauca by helicopter from Palmira.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected to be the man who led the oldest guerrilla in the world, so they asked him to carry the decadactilar card of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
However, when he arrived with the investigation team at the site of the body, he did not recognize it by its physical appearance, as it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He was beardless, dressed like a local peasant, without glasses and much thinner.
But the tracks don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a transplanter and a flashlight, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse with those on the card.
His eye didn't fail him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the Puerto Tejada man was in charge of confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinzón, that he was the top FARC leader.
In search of the footprint
For a dactyloscopist from Sijín de Cali, the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos gave to Eliazar González, in the press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
A lot of people don't know our work.
Fingerprinting is an exact science, with no margin for error, that can become the key to solving crimes.
Apart from identifying dead bodies, lofoscopists support investigations into crimes such as robbery and murder and confirm the identity of captured persons.
When caught, many criminals present false ID cards or are undocumented.
We take their fingerprints and run them through the database.
The investigator said that in one case of theft, he had to remove a piece of the wall of a house, because the thief had put his hand on it to take out a safe full of jewels and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not suitable surfaces to take a fingerprint, but in that case we were able to obtain the imprint of the whole hand and identify the offender, who had participated in different robberies", he recalled.
Footprints can also rule out or reassert suspects in homicide cases.
A man was found dead recently, with liquor bottles all around him.
Through investigation, it was determined that a relative could be a suspect in the crime, and indeed, a fingerprint on the bottle matched.
While this doesn't guarantee that he was the killer, it does place him at the crime scene.
A CTI fingerprint specialist explained that "the fingerprints are removed with chemical or physical reagents" on the objects.
When they do appear, a transplanter or tape is used to lift them.
After this, the prints are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registrar.
"The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians", said the CTI expert.
He made it clear that not everything is as shown on the television show CSI.
Just as all that glitters is not gold, not everything that is touched becomes a fingerprint.
However, if it can be used, if the respective comparison is made.
