Tokyo has been entrusted to the domestic market, while the yen - the Japanese currency - has become one of the 'safe haven' assets chosen by investors fleeing the eurozone debt crisis and the murky prospects for the US, a privilege that weighs like a stone on the accounts of exporting companies.
