The Austrian Government's scheme is similar to the 'German model', as Germany was the first European country to adopt this type of 'rule'.
Before 2017, the structural government deficit should decrease by 0,75% of gross domestic product (GDP) each year and, from 2017, the structural government deficit of the federal state should not exceed 0,35% of GDP each year, while the regional states, as well as the municipalities, should present balanced budgets.
The objective is to reduce public debt by 2020/2021 under the 60% criterion laid down by the Maastricht Treaty.
